### Phase 3 — Ticket assignment + status workflow + histories
###
### Builds on Phase 2. Promote agent/admin roles via SQL once after registration:
###
###   UPDATE users SET role='agent' WHERE email='agent@example.com';
###   UPDATE users SET role='admin' WHERE email='admin@example.com';

@host = http://localhost:8080
@customerEmail = customer@example.com
@agentEmail    = agent@example.com
@adminEmail    = admin@example.com
@password      = password123

@customerToken = paste-customer-token
@agentToken    = paste-agent-token
@adminToken    = paste-admin-token
@ticketId      = paste-ticket-uuid
@categoryId    = paste-category-uuid
@agentUserId   = paste-agent-int64

### 1. Login as customer (paste access_token into @customerToken)
POST {{host}}/api/v1/auth/login
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "email": "{{customerEmail}}",
  "password": "{{password}}"
}

### 2. Login as admin / agent the same way → fill @adminToken / @agentToken / @agentUserId

### 3. List categories (paste a UUID into @categoryId)
GET {{host}}/api/v1/ticket-categories
Authorization: Bearer {{customerToken}}

### 4. Create ticket
POST {{host}}/api/v1/tickets
Content-Type: application/json
Authorization: Bearer {{customerToken}}

{
  "title": "Cannot log in from mobile",
  "description": "The application rejects valid credentials when I tap Login.",
  "category_id": "{{categoryId}}",
  "priority": "high"
}

### 5. Try to move unassigned ticket open -> in_progress (admin) — EXPECTED 422
PATCH {{host}}/api/v1/tickets/{{ticketId}}/status
Authorization: Bearer {{adminToken}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "status": "in_progress"
}

### 6. Assign agent
PATCH {{host}}/api/v1/tickets/{{ticketId}}/assign
Authorization: Bearer {{adminToken}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "agent_id": {{agentUserId}},
  "note": "Assigned to the support agent for investigation"
}

### 7. Agent moves open -> in_progress
PATCH {{host}}/api/v1/tickets/{{ticketId}}/status
Authorization: Bearer {{agentToken}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "status": "in_progress",
  "note": "Investigation started"
}

### 8. Agent resolves
PATCH {{host}}/api/v1/tickets/{{ticketId}}/status
Authorization: Bearer {{agentToken}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "status": "resolved"
}

### 9. Admin closes
PATCH {{host}}/api/v1/tickets/{{ticketId}}/status
Authorization: Bearer {{adminToken}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "status": "closed"
}

### 10. Customer reopens their own closed ticket
PATCH {{host}}/api/v1/tickets/{{ticketId}}/status
Authorization: Bearer {{customerToken}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "status": "reopened",
  "note": "Issue happened again"
}

### 11. Read histories (chronological)
GET {{host}}/api/v1/tickets/{{ticketId}}/histories
Authorization: Bearer {{customerToken}}

### 12. Agent's assigned-to-me list with status filter
GET {{host}}/api/v1/tickets?scope=assigned_to_me&status=reopened
Authorization: Bearer {{agentToken}}

### 13. Customer's own list (default scope)
GET {{host}}/api/v1/tickets?scope=created_by_me
Authorization: Bearer {{customerToken}}
